definition.value: A suburb of Perth, Western Australia, located within the City of Armadale.
A light industrial suburb of Perth, Western Australia. Its Local Government Area is the City of Stirling.
A suburb of Perth, Western Australia, located within the City of Subiaco and 4 km west of the Central business district.
A northern suburb and regional city in Perth, Western Australia. Its Local Government Area is the City of Joondalup, Western Australia.
A suburb of Perth, Western Australia, situated 23 km north of Perth GPO. Edgewater was approved as a suburb name in 1974, and its Local Government Area is the City of Joondalup.

A suburb 18 km south of the central business district of Perth, the capital of Western Australia, and 8 km from the Indian Ocean. The suburb is located within the City of Cockburn local government area.
A suburb located in Perth, Western Australia.
A province of Nagorno-Karabakh Republic. In 1991 the parliament of Azerbaijan abolished Martuni province, incorporating its territory into the neighbouring Azerbaijani rayon of Khojavend.
A disputed region, formerly a district of Azerbaijan SSR outside of Nagorno-Karabakh Autonomous Oblast.
A rayon of Azerbaijan. It surrounds the city of Shusha, in Nagorno-Karabakh, and is completely under Armenian control.
A province of Nagorno-Karabakh Republic. It forms the southern border of Nagorno-Karabakh.
One of the eight provinces of the unrecognised Nagorno-Karabakh Republic (NKR), coterminous with the Azerbaijani rayon of Khojali.

A province of the de facto independent Nagorno-Karabakh Republic. Its territory is a de jure part of Azerbaijan, divided between the Tartar and Kelbajar rayons after Azerbaijan's abolition of the Nagorno-Karabakh Autonomous Oblast in 1991.
A populated place. A town in the State of Rajasthan in India. Pushkar lies on the shore of Pushkar Lake.
A populated place. A town in Nainital district in the State of Uttarakhand, India situated at an altitude of 1370 meters above sea level and is about 22 km from Nainital.
A populated place. A town located in Sindh province of Pakistan.
A mountain village in Swat, located in the Buner District of the North-West Frontier Province of Pakistan.
A cataract on the River Nile in Sudan near the confluence with the Atbara River.
A cataract on the River Nile in the Manasir Desert, Sudan. It will be flooded by the Merowe Dam from 2006.
A former cataract on the River Nile in Sudan that was in Nubia and is now submerged in Lake Nasser.
A cataract on the River Nile in Sudan near Tombos.
A cataract on the River Nile in Sudan where it cuts through the Sabaluka pluton near Bagrawiyah.
A cataract on the River Nile near Aswan.
A populated place. A city in the province of Girona in northeastern Catalonia, Spain.

A river that rises in the town of Novomoskovsk 60 km southeast from Tula, southeast of Moscow, and flows for a distance of about 1,950 km to the Sea of Azov. From its source, the river first flows southeast to Voronezh, then southwest to its mouth. The main city on the river is Rostov on Don, its main tributary, the Donets.
A river. Discharges to the Bay of Biscay.
A populated place.

A river of southern France. Its length is 160 km. Its source is in the Cevennes mountains. It reaches the Mediterranean Sea near Agde. The Herault flows through the following departements: Herault and Gard.

Un fleuve cotier du sud de la France, de 76 km de long, qui coule en Roussillon, dans les departements de l'Aude et des Pyrenees-Orientales. L'Agly prend sa source au col de Linas, pres du Pech de Bugarach dans les Corbieres, departement de l'Aude. Il passe ensuite passe dans les Pyrenees-Orientales par les gorges de Galamus, arrose Saint-Paul-de-Fenouillet, il est retenu par un barrage, a Caramany, passe e Estagel ou il recoit le Verdouble et se jette dans la mer Mediterranee au sud de la station balneaire du Barcares.

A river that rises on the flanks of Puy de Sancy (1885 m) in the mountains of Auvergne, from the confluence of two small torrents above the town of Mont-Dore: the Dore and the Dogne. It flows generally west about 500 km through the Limousin and Perigord regions before flowing into the Gironde, its common estuary with the Garonne, at the "Ambes beak", in the north of the city of Bordeaux.
